        "timestamp": 1773093491,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. Trump has 'very few' options to keep energy prices down in the short term, analyst says Middle East Issued on: 09/03/2026 - 22:58 Modified: 09/03/2026 - 23:06 Speaking with FRANCE 24's Sharon Gaffney, Peter McNally, Global Head of Sector Analysts at Third Bridge, says that \"the duration of the outage in the Middle East is going to be the biggest factor\" in the G7's decision to tap into strategic oil reserves, adding that US President Donald Trump has \"very few\" options to keep energy prices down in the short term \"other than to make demand go lower\". 'There never was a plan' behind war in Iran, analyst says 09/03/2026 Middle East Trump calls on Australia to give asylum to Iranian women's soccer players 09/03/2026 Middle East Erdogan warns Iran against 'provocative steps' after second missile intercepted 09/03/2026 Middle East Bahrain says Iranian drone attack damages water desalination plant 09/03/2026 Middle East Explosions heard across Doha, sirens sound in Bahrain as Iran strikes Gulf neighbours 09/03/2026 Middle East Macron says France, allies preparing 'defensive' mission to reopen Strait of Hormuz 09/03/2026 Middle East Israel accused of using white phosphorus in Lebanese residential areas 09/03/2026 Middle East Macron announces ‘purely defensive’ mission to reopen Strait of Hormuz 09/03/2026 Middle East What will Iran's new Ayatollah Mojtaba Khamenei be in charge of? 09/03/2026 Middle East"
